[1859, 11-25] Ms.A.9.2.29.79

Argyle, George Douglas Campbell, duke of, to MWC. “The great experiment
of Free Labour in the South, which seems to be so successful in Texas,
... is very important and encouraging. ... As to the {u}feeling{/u} in
England you cannot doubt that it is {u}entirely{/u} with you ... We have
been painfully interested in the Harper’s Ferry Affair ...”


